*(''chiefly British''): '''[[encyclopaedia]]'''. The spelling '''encyclopedia''' is standard in American and Canadian English, accepted in Australian and International English, and is also common in British English.

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''[[encyclopædia]]''' < {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἐγκύκλιος παιδεία]]}}''' (enkyklios paideia) < '''{{polytonic|[[ἐγκύκλιος]]}}''' (enkyklios) "circular, rounded, round" < '''{{polytonic|[[κύκλος]]}}''' (kyklos) "circle" + '''{{polytonic|[[παιδεία]]}}''' (paideia) "the rearing of a child", or "education", from '''{{polytonic|[[παιδίον]]}}''' (paidion) "child".

